  <chunk id="c24060d084e314b214e061995b5528b2e0071e31.c1" text="Background: The functional role of ELR-positive CXC chemokines during viral -induced demyelination was assessed. Inoculation of the neuroattenuated JHM strain of mouse hepatitis virus (JHMV) into the CNS of susceptible mice results in an acute encephalomyelitis that evolves into a chronic demyelinating disease, modeling white matter pathology observed in the human demyelinating disease Multiple Sclerosis.">
    <entity charOffset="85-98" id="c24060d084e314b214e061995b5528b2e0071e31.c1.e0" ontology_id="HP_0011096" text="demyelination" type="phenotype"/>
